        "title": {
          "english": "Asking about someone's job"
        },
        "text": "To ask someone 'What is your job?' in Darija, you can use a direct phrase. This question can be used for both males and females.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "آش هي خدمتك؟",
            "english": "What is your job?",
            "transliteration": "Ash hiya khdemtek?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Stating your job (Male)"
        },
        "text": "When a male wants to say 'I am a...', he uses 'Ana' (أنا) followed by the masculine job title.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا طبيب.",
            "english": "I am a doctor (male).",
            "transliteration": "Ana tbib."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
